Convener of The Platform, Poju Oyemade, has reiterated his commitment to using the annual discourse to foster national development. The event scheduled for tomorrow, May 1, at the Covenant, beside National Theatre Iganmu, Lagos is aimed at stimulating and challenging the mind, will and intellect of the citizens. With the theme ‘Drivers, Enablers and Obstacles to our Growth’ Oyemade said this year’s edition is examining growth, its drivers and obstacles at personal, organisational and national level, while looking at the things that will propel growth. Speakers includes chairman, Board of Directors, First Bank of Nigeria, Ibukun Awosika; President, Africa Institute of Technology, Dr. Ndubuisi Ekekwe, Managing Partner, Sahel Consulting, Ndidi Nwuneli founder, B. Adedipe Associates, Dr. Biodun Adedipe; founder, Pando Daily, Sarah Lacy; chairman, Editorial board, Thisday Newspapers, Segun Adeniyi; and Dr. Anil Guta.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .